---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Contributing — MeshTexas"
  description="How to submit an article to MeshTexas — categories, regions, and the review process."
>
  <div class="page-intro">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h1>Contributing Articles</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Anyone can submit an article — here's how it works, and what the fields mean.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="about-section tint">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Go to <a href="/admin/">/admin</a> and log in with your GitHub account — no special access required. You'll get a simple editor with Draft and Ready to Review columns. Write your article, move it to Ready to Review when it's done, and it becomes a real submission for a MeshTexas admin to look over.</p>
        <p>Nothing you submit goes live automatically. An admin reviews every submission before it's published — so don't worry about getting something wrong, it won't reach the site until someone checks it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2>Categories</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>How-To</strong> — setup guides, configuration walkthroughs, anything that helps someone do something with their device or the network.</li>
          <li><strong>Buildout / Infrastructure</strong> — updates on new repeaters, expanding coverage, or network changes.</li>
          <li><strong>Community</strong> — spotlights, partnerships, events, or anything about the people involved.</li>
          <li><strong>Announcement</strong> — site or policy changes, anything MeshTexas-wide.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section tint">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2>Regions</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>If your article is about a specific area, tag it with that region's IATA code — the same codes used on the <a href="/connect">Connect</a> page (<code>SAT</code> for San Antonio, <code>AUS</code> for Austin, and so on). You can tag more than one, or leave it blank if the article applies statewide.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2>One Thing to Know</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>The <a href="/host-a-node">Host a Node</a> section is managed by MeshTexas admins directly, not open for general submissions — if you have something for it, <a href="mailto:info@meshtexas.org">email us</a> instead of submitting through /admin.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
